5-68:It is due to the fact that miss probability is improved by indexing all the hypotheses provided by the WCNs .
5-69:This observation confirms the results shown by Mamou et al .
5-70:[17] in the context of spoken document retrieval .
5-71:The ATWV that we have obtained is close to the MTWV; we have combined our ranking model with appropriate threshold θ to eliminate results with lower score .
5-72:Therefore, the effect of false alarms added by WCNs is reduced .
5-73:WCN phonetic approach was used in the recent NIST STD evaluation and received the highest overall ranking among eleven participants .
5-74:For comparison, the system that ranked at the third place, obtained an ATWV of 0.8238 for BNEWS, 0.6652 for CTS and 0.1103 for CONFMTG .
5-75:4.6 Influence of the duration of the query on the retrieval performance We have analysed the retrieval performance according to the average duration of the occurrences in the manual transcripts .
5-76:The query set was divided into three different quantiles according to the duration; we have reported in Table 5 ATWV and MTWV according to the duration .
5-77:We can see that we performed better on longer queries .
5-78:One of the reasons is the fact that the ASR system is more accurate on long words .
5-79:Hence, it was justified to boost the score of the results with the exponent γn, as explained in Section 3.4.3, according to the length of the query .
